OL,6,FThe cuts to benefits went further than
OL,7,Fhad initially been announced just one
OL,8,Fweek prior - a response to the OBR
OL,9,Fhalving the UK growth forecast to 1% -
OL,10,Freducing the fiscal headroom the
OL,11,Fgovernment had to work with.
OL,13,FPaul Johnson, director of the IFS,
OL,14,Fsaid these extra changes risked
OL,15,F"undermining" the chancellor's
OL,16,Finsistence that these cuts were about
OL,17,Freforming the welfare system.
